^^^^^^^^^^Who is the audience for such ephemera ?  Whoever passes by.  Why does humour play such a role in learning about communicating to other ? Because delight in wit and its application is hard to simulate.  That is, even children may get an honest response instead of one based on condescension and according them special privelege as incomplete persons.

^^^^^^^^^^Notice that we have emphasized writing which has potential for engaging an audience.  We have not mentioned anywhere the role of teacher as assignment-giver and paper-corrector.  The point is that the child will profit from more from a more frequent and casual interaction with people who care more about the content of his work that he would from scholastic assignments and corrections.


