1Conclusions0

^^^^^^^^^^Dare we prediuct that from such experiences children will learn more about writing than they do now ?  There are three possible claims: ALL children will learn something (this is a supplement fort current curriculum); SOME children will learn more than they do now (this is supplement for some special class of students); ALL children will learn more than they do now (this is a replacement for the standard curriculum).

^^^^^^^^^^We can conclude that these thre papers offer an alternative VISION to writing instruction as practised today.  As a supplement to the standard curriculum it will not be harmful.  It deserves to be examined as an alternative because it strives to make writing useful and meaningful to the child while he is learning how to do it.  
